# =================
# SESSION STRING SETUP GUIDE
# =================
# 
# üîë HOW TO GET SESSION STRING:
# 
# 1. USE YOUR SESSION GENERATOR:
#    - Go to your session generator website/bot
#    - Enter your WhatsApp number (with country code)
#    - Scan the QR code with WhatsApp
#    - Copy the session string (like "malvin~3EB0A1B2C3D...")
# 
# 2. SET SESSION STRING:
#    Replace "your-session-string-here" above with your actual session string
#    Example: SESSION_STRING=malvin~3EB0A1B2C3D4E5F6...
# 
# 3. SET SESSION ID:
#    Choose a unique identifier for your bot
#    Example: SESSION_ID=my-groq-bot
# 
# 4. DEPLOY:
#    Your bot will automatically authenticate using the session string
#    No QR scanning or file management needed!
# 
# üîÑ SESSION STRING VS FILES:
# 
# ‚úÖ SESSION STRING (Recommended):
#    - Easy to deploy and manage
#    - Just copy/paste the string
#    - Perfect for cloud platforms
#    - No file management needed
# 
# üìÅ SESSION FILES (Alternative):
#    - Traditional method
#    - Need to upload multiple files
#    - More complex deployment
#    - Leave SESSION_STRING empty to use this method
# 
# üìã EXAMPLE SESSION STRINGS:
# - malvin~3EB0A1B2C3D4E5F6...
# - groq~eyJjcmVkcyI6eyJub2lzZUtl...
# - session~base64encodeddata...
# 
# üîß MULTIPLE BOTS:
# Each bot needs:
# - Unique SESSION_STRING (from different WhatsApp numbers)
# - Unique SESSION_ID 
# - Example:
#   Bot 1: SESSION_ID=groq-bot-main, SESSION_STRING=malvin~ABC...
#   Bot 2: SESSION_ID=groq-bot-test, SESSION_STRING=malvin~XYZ...
# 
# üõ†Ô∏è TROUBLESHOOTING:
# - "Invalid session string" ‚Üí Get a fresh session from generator
# - "Session expired" ‚Üí WhatsApp was logged out, generate new session
# - "Connection failed" ‚Üí Check if WhatsApp number is active
# 
# üîê SECURITY:
# - Keep SESSION_STRING private and secure
# - Never share your session string
# - Session string gives full WhatsApp access
# - Use environment variables, never hardcode in files
#
# üí° QUICK START:
# 1. Get session string from your generator
# 2. Replace SESSION_STRING=your-session-string-here with actual value
# 3. Set unique SESSION_ID
